  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "If you suspect that someone has blocked you on Facebook Messenger, there are several signs you can look for to help confirm your suspicion. However, it's important to note that these indicators are not definitive proof of being blocked, as they could also result from other factors like the person deactivating their account or adjusting their privacy settings. Here are some common signs that someone may have blocked you on Messenger:\n\n1. **Messages Not Delivered:**\n   - **Sent Status:** When you send a message, it might show as \"Sent\" but never change to \"Delivered\" or \"Seen.\" This could indicate that the recipient can no longer receive your messages.\n   \n2. **Profile Invisibility:**\n   - **Search Issues:** If you try to search for the person\u2019s name in Messenger or on Facebook and their profile doesn\u2019t appear, they might have blocked you.\n   - **Profile Picture and Status:** You may no longer see their profile picture, online status, or any updates to their status and stories.\n\n3. **Inability to Make Voice or Video Calls:**\n   - **Call Failures:** Attempts to initiate a voice or video call via Messenger may fail or not go through at all.\n\n4. **Previous Conversations Disappear or Restrict:**\n   - **Conversation History:** In some cases, the entire conversation history may disappear from your Messenger app. Alternatively, you might only see limited information like the message \"This person is unavailable.\"\n\n5. **No Reaction or Interaction:**\n   - **Engagement:** If the person used to interact with your posts, comments, or messages and suddenly stops without any apparent reason, it might be a sign of being blocked.\n\n6. **Unable to Tag or Add to Groups:**\n   - **Tagging Issues:** If you try to tag the person in a post or add them to a group and it doesn\u2019t work, this could indicate that you've been blocked.\n\n7. **No Longer on Your Friends List:**\n   - **Friend Status:** If you check your Facebook friends list and no longer see the person, they might have unfriended you or blocked you.\n\n### How to Confirm\n\nWhile the above signs can suggest that you\u2019ve been blocked, here are a few steps to help you confirm:\n\n- **Check from Another Account:** Try searching for the person using a different Facebook account or ask a mutual friend to see if their profile is visible.\n  \n- **Visit Their Facebook Profile Directly:** If you can\u2019t access their profile or see any content, it might indicate that you\u2019ve been blocked or that they\u2019ve deleted/deactivated their account.\n\n- **Review Your Messenger List:** If their profile no longer appears in your Messenger contacts and you cannot find any past conversations, this strengthens the possibility of being blocked.\n\n### Consider Other Possibilities\n\nRemember that technical glitches, privacy setting changes, or the person simply deactivating their account temporarily can produce similar signs. If you\u2019re unsure, reaching out through another communication channel (like email or another messaging platform) might help clarify the situation.\n\n### Respect Privacy\n\nIf someone has chosen to block you, it's important to respect their decision and privacy. Avoid trying to circumvent the block through other means, as this can violate Facebook's terms of service and may lead to further issues.\n\n---\n\n**Note:** Facebook's features and policies can change over time. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, consider visiting [Facebook's Help Center](https://www.facebook.com/help/) or consulting their official support resources.",
